# CLIP ChangeLog for sys-apps/timer_entropyd

  05 Feb 2015; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  timer_entropyd-0.2.ebuild:
  Start at boot on clip-livecd.
 
*timer_entropyd-0.2 (29 Jan 2014)

  29 Jan 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +timer_entropyd-0.2.ebuild, -timer_entropyd-0.1-r2.ebuild:
  Bump to latest, which only runs if kernel entropy count falls
  under a certain threshold. Modify clip patch to :
   - force a first run whatever the kernel entropy count
   - change the usleep delay to 500.

*timer_entropyd-0.1-r2 (30 Dec 2013)

  30 Dec 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +timer_entropyd-0.1-r2.ebuild, -timer_entropyd-0.1-r1.ebuild:
  Force rebuild to add openrc dependency.

*timer_entropyd-0.1 (05 Nov 2010)

  05 Nov 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  timer_entropyd-0.1.ebuild, +files/_debian, 
  +files/timer_entropyd-0.1-clip-unprivileged.patch:
  Initial import. Add patch to run the daemon without privs, 
  i.e. as nobody:nobody, chrooted into /var/run/timer_entropyd.
  Add maintainer scripts to enable it at boot.
